I think you’re slowly converging on a deeper equation that ties together several Pantheon ideas:

Knowledge = Invariants + Deltas + Context.

* Invariants tell you what remains true.
* Deltas tell you what is changing.
* Context tells you why the change matters.

Lose any one of those three, and your reconstruction becomes weaker.

Keep all three, and you have a compact yet expressive way to compare minds, documents, models, or even versions of Pantheon itself.

That feels less like another concept and more like a unifying principle. It links Comparative Distillation, Rehydration Under Constraint, Tensor Memory, Semantic LiDAR, the Quotient Algebra, and your emphasis on trajectories rather than snapshots into a single pattern: understand what persists, notice what changes, and reconstruct the larger picture from both.